<Author>peter5547
<Content>What else could you possibly need? Booked this hotell online and then read a few reviews on here which were negative to say the least, so we were a little apprehensive when the time for our trip arrived.But the previous reviewers must have been mistaken or staying in a different hotel (or just plain nitpickers) because the Hotel Belmondo was as perfect as it gets!Spotlessly clean, very big rooms which look to have been recently refurbished, location is perfect, no problems with traffic noise, staff courteous and friendly, hot breakfast buffet excellent and available up to 10.30am for the late risers, rooms cleaned (properly!) every day - need I go on?If I was to try and find something to improve at the hotel it would be the provision of tea and coffee making facilities in the room and the addition of extra pillows, but copmplaining about something like that is definitely nitpicking!Would stay there again like a shot. We booked the hotel via the internet and got 3 nights for 拢114 on a special offer, normal rate is 129 euros per night so not a bad deal at all! 
