<Author>avecarvalho
<Content>OK hotel. I was going to stay at Boulevard hotel, but they overbooked me!! They managed to find a room in Hotel Belmondo, half a block away from Boulevard hotel.Its is an old hotel that has been renewed some years ago. Its spacial configuration is a little bit weird and take a lot of walk to get to some of the rooms, in particular those in the right wing (worse if you have lots of luggage). The staff is just professional, not friendly.My room was more like a pod, extremely small (beware, all the rooms located on corners tend to be that small). Everything seemed a little improvised and the noise from the street (Ku'damm) was very loud. It was clean, though.The positive thing about the hotel is it`s location, near Zoo Hauptbahnhof and the best shopping area in Berlin. And it has free wi-fi internet connection on the lobby too. 
